comment: Black (LAL) legally contests Cousins' (SAC) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Black (LAL) sets the screen on Collison (SAC) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Black (LAL) makes incidental contact with Cousins (SAC) in the post.
[Observable in enhanced video] Cousins (SAC) moves his pivot foot.
Black (LAL) makes contact with Cousins' (SAC) arms that affects his post shot attempt.
Barnes (SAC) clears the lane within three seconds.
SAC do not exit the timeout in a timely manner.
Barnes (SAC) and Young (LAL) briefly engage and separate during rebounding.
Nance Jr. (LAL) makes contact with Cousins' (SAC) body that affects his post shot attempt.
Williams (LAL) makes incidental foot to foot contact with Collison (SAC) that does not affect his ability to defend.
[Detectable with stop watch] Clarkson (LAL) is in the paint without actively guarding an opponent for longer than three seconds.
Cousins (SAC) and Nance Jr. (LAL) briefly engage and separate during rebounding.
Barnes (SAC) and Nance Jr. (LAL) briefly engage and separate during rebounding.
[Observable in enhanced video] Mozgov (LAL) enters the paint area prior to the free throw being released.
Nance Jr. (LAL) makes contact with Cousins' (SAC) arms that affects his shot attempt.
Tolliver (SAC) and Mozgov (LAL) make incidental contact with one another during rebounding.
Tolliver (SAC) and Ingram (LAL) briefly engage and separate during rebounding.
Mozgov (LAL) sets the screen on Collison (SAC) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
